 BAFTA Award for Best Makeup and Hair  This is a list of the nominees and winners for the BAFTA Award for Best Makeup and Hair given out by the British Academy of Film and Television Arts.  2017:  2016: "Florence Foster Jenkins" – J. Roy Helland and Daniel Phillips  2015: "" – Damian Martin and Lesley Vanderwalt  2014: "The Grand Budapest Hotel" – Frances Hannon and Mark Coulier  2013: "American Hustle" – Evelyne Noraz and Kathrine Gordon  2012: "Les Misérables" – Lisa Westcott  2011: "The Iron Lady" – Marese Langan  2010: "Alice in Wonderland" – Valli O'Reilly and Paul Gooch  2009: "The Young Victoria" – Jenny Shircore  2008: "The Curious Case of Benjamin Button" – Jean Black and Colleen Callaghan  2007: "La Vie en Rose (La môme)" – Jan Archibald and Didier Lavergne  2006: "Pan's Labyrinth (El laberinto del fauno)" – José Quetglás and Blanca Sánchez  2005: "" – Howard Berger, Nikki Gooley, and Greg Nicotero  2004: "The Aviator" – Kathryn Blondell, Siân Grigg, and Morag Ross  2003: "" – Ve Neill and Martin Samuel  2002: "Frida" – Judy Chin, Beatrice De Alba, John E. Jackson, and Regina Reyes  2001: "" – Peter King, Peter Owen, and Richard Taylor  2000: "Dr. Seuss' How the Grinch Stole Christmas" – Rick Baker, Toni G, Sylvia Nava, Gail Ryan, and Kazuhiro Tsuji  1999: "Topsy-Turvy" – Christine Blundell  1998: "Elizabeth" – Jenny Shircore  1997: "The Wings of the Dove" – Sallie Jaye and Jan Archibald  1996: "The Nutty Professor" – Rick Baker and David LeRoy Anderson  1995: "The Madness of King George" – Lisa Westcott  1994: "The Adventures of Priscilla, Queen of the Desert" – Cassie Hanlon, Angela Conte, and Strykermeyer  1993: "Orlando" – Morag Ross  1992: "The Last of the Mohicans" – Peter King  1991: "Cyrano de Bergerac" – Jean-Pierre Eychenne and Michèle Burke  1990: "Dick Tracy" – John Caglione Jr. and Doug Drexler  1989: "The Adventures of Baron Munchausen" – Maggie Weston, Fabrizio Sforza, and Pam Meager  1988: "The Last Emperor" – Fabrizio Sforza  1987: "The Name of the Rose" – Hasso von Hugo  1986: "Ran" – Tameyuki Aimi, Chihako Naito, and Noriko Takamizawa  1985: "Amadeus" – Paul LeBlanc and Dick Smith  1984 "" – Paul Engelen, Peter Frampton, Rick Baker, and Joan Hills  1983: "Tootsie" – Dorothy J. Pearl, George Masters, C. Romania Ford, and Allen Weisinger  1982: "Quest for Fire" – Sarah Monzani, Christopher Tucker, and Michèle Bur